In the same way as you can "Allow all statuses to transition to this one", it would be good if you could apply this same operation to outbound transitions.

 

As an example, we have a status called "On Hold". It should be possible for a user to transition to this status from any other status, and also to transition back again (to any other status). 

 

The first part is easy: simply check "Allow all statuses to transition to this one". On the reverse though, you need to add individual transitions back to each status. It can be a little time-consuming if you have a big workflow with many statuses, and inevitably makes the workflow diagram look like spaghetti; very difficult to read.

